@page "/docs/extensions/svg-chart"

<Seo Canonical="/docs/extensions/svg-chart" Title="Blazorise SVG Chart component" Description="Learn how to use native Blazorise SVG chart components, including column, bar, line, area, pie, doughnut, polar area, radar, scatter, and bubble charts." />

<DocsPageTitle Path="Extensions/SVG Chart">
    Blazorise SVG Chart component
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Full C# and Blazor charting, rendered with native SVG.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    The SVG chart extension renders charts directly from C# data, options, callbacks, and child components. It supports declarative data binding through child components and explicit data models for imperative scenarios.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Supported chart types are:
</DocsPageParagraph>

<UnorderedList>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgColumnChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgBarChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgLineChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgAreaChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgPieChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgDoughnutChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgPolarAreaChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgRadarChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgScatterChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>SvgBubbleChart</Code></UnorderedListItem>
</UnorderedList>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    To use the SVG chart components, install the <Code>Blazorise.Charts.Svg</Code> package first.
</DocsPageParagraph>

